result.execSummary:
The defendant Thurman Darnell Kimble was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Thurman Darnell Kimble in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Clerk;ds

Sentencing proceeds.   State advises the Court they have complied with victim notification.  Statements by counsel and defendant.  

Count 1:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 6 months at the House of Correction with Huber privileges for work and drug treatment or counseling and 1 day credit.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years.

Count 2:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 6 months at the House of Correction - consecutive  to Count 1 - with Huber privileges for work and drug treatment or counseling.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years - concurrent.

CONDITIONS:  1) no violations of the criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges with payments commencing 11-1-15 or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant; 3) do not use or possess illegally controlled substances; 4) random screening; 5) AODA, treatment or program; 6) maintain employment; 7) As to Count 2: pay restitution of $3,029 to the Home Depot with payments commencing 11-1-15 or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant.

Court advises the defendant any possession or use of any illegally controlled substance, alcohol forfeits the release privileges. 

Appeal rights given.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Copy given to the defendant.
Restitution Worksheet received and filed./ds

Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, victim, a friend or relative of the defendant and defendant.  Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 72 hours in advance of sentencing.  Restitution will be addressed at that time.
